1
00:00:01,084 --> 00:00:04,337
[Axl] <i>You're giving us</i>
<i>these weapons for free?</i>

2
00:00:04,421 --> 00:00:05,422
<i>What's the catch?</i>

3
00:00:05,505 --> 00:00:07,799
[Felix] <i>You're going to rob a bank</i>
<i>using those weapons.</i>

4
00:00:07,882 --> 00:00:09,592
We'll split the money 50-50.

5
00:00:09,676 --> 00:00:13,388
[Felix] <i>Just make sure you don't screw up.</i>

6
00:00:13,471 --> 00:00:15,473
[Norhana] <i>Do you know Jamilah?</i>

7
00:00:15,557 --> 00:00:17,017
[nurse] <i>She’s still inside.</i>

8
00:00:17,100 --> 00:00:18,727
[Jalil] <i>We need to split up.</i>

9
00:00:18,810 --> 00:00:19,936
I'll go this way.

10
00:00:21,521 --> 00:00:23,398
[Tommy] <i>Leave me. Save yourself.</i>

11
00:00:23,481 --> 00:00:24,899
<i>I'll just slow you down.</i>

12
00:00:24,983 --> 00:00:26,151
[Jovi] <i>I'll come back for you.</i>

13
00:00:26,234 --> 00:00:27,902
[Lara] <i>I found Miss Teresa!</i>

14
00:00:27,986 --> 00:00:29,362
<i>They have another captive.</i>

15
00:00:29,446 --> 00:00:30,822
[in English] A Muslim girl.

16
00:00:31,448 --> 00:00:34,117
[Jalil] <i>Reyes, save that hostage.</i>

17
00:00:34,200 --> 00:00:35,285
<i>I'll save your mother.</i>

18
00:00:35,368 --> 00:00:37,162
[Marcus] <i>Leave the girl alone. Fight me.</i>

19
00:00:37,245 --> 00:00:39,372
- [Jovi grunts]
- [Jalil] <i>Hostage secured.</i>

20
00:00:39,456 --> 00:00:40,832
<i>Your mother is safe.</i>

21
00:00:41,624 --> 00:00:42,667
- [grunts loudly]
- [shouts]

22
00:00:42,751 --> 00:00:45,086
[Marcus, in English] <i>Hostage clear.</i>
<i>Target secured.</i>

23
00:00:46,629 --> 00:00:48,548
[Jalil] <i>I infiltrated Marcus Reyes's group</i>

24
00:00:48,631 --> 00:00:52,343
<i>to find out the truth and to find Father.</i>

25
00:00:52,427 --> 00:00:55,638
<i>Whoever is behind all of this,</i>
<i>they are powerful.</i>

26
00:00:55,722 --> 00:00:58,099
[Jamilah] <i>I found out that Marcus Reyes</i>

27
00:00:58,183 --> 00:01:00,518
<i>is trying to uncover what really</i>
<i>happened on the island.</i>

28
00:01:00,602 --> 00:01:03,813
He believes that someone
hijacked their mission.

29
00:01:03,897 --> 00:01:06,232
[Marcus] <i>The criminals used an RPG.</i>

30
00:01:06,316 --> 00:01:08,401
<i>How could they have such a weapon?</i>

31
00:01:08,485 --> 00:01:11,196
I'm not a part of the syndicate!

32
00:01:11,279 --> 00:01:14,657
[Datu Rahman] <i>My silence</i>
<i>will keep my children safe.</i>

33
00:01:14,741 --> 00:01:17,285
<i>You cannot find out the truth.</i>

34
00:01:17,368 --> 00:01:19,454
[Felix] <i>I've cleaned it up.</i>
<i>Even the youngest brother is dead.</i>

35
00:01:19,537 --> 00:01:21,372
[Lara] <i>I don't need to know that.</i>

36
00:01:21,456 --> 00:01:22,832
I'm just doing my job, Lara.

37
00:01:22,916 --> 00:01:26,628
[Felix] <i>Don't forget</i>
<i>how important our mission is.</i>

38
00:01:27,212 --> 00:01:30,256
<i>We need to protect Lara.</i>

39
00:01:30,340 --> 00:01:34,427
<i>Maybe someday she'll learn to love us.</i>

40
00:01:34,511 --> 00:01:37,138
[Jalil] <i>I’m going</i>
<i>up against powerful people.</i>

41
00:01:37,222 --> 00:01:40,016
<i>I know that in the end,</i>
<i>justice will prevail.</i>

42
00:01:40,099 --> 00:01:42,936
<i>Help me find Father,</i>
<i>so we can be together again</i>

43
00:01:43,019 --> 00:01:46,231
<i>and return to our peaceful lives.</i>

44
00:01:46,314 --> 00:01:49,818
[tense music playing]

45
00:01:49,901 --> 00:01:53,238
[mysterious theme music playing]

46
00:02:05,083 --> 00:02:07,710
- [people screaming]
- [cop] Take cover!

47
00:02:07,794 --> 00:02:09,212
- [cop 1] Get down!
- [cop 2, in English] Take cover!

48
00:02:09,295 --> 00:02:10,713
- [cop 3] Get down!
- [overlapping shouting]

49
00:02:10,797 --> 00:02:12,132
Oh my goodness.

50
00:02:12,215 --> 00:02:15,385
What happened to Jamilah
at the hospital was terrible.

51
00:02:15,468 --> 00:02:16,636
And now this?

52
00:02:16,719 --> 00:02:19,222
Then the hostage-takers were killed.

53
00:02:19,305 --> 00:02:21,599
How horrendous.

54
00:02:21,683 --> 00:02:23,226
That is terrifying.

55
00:02:24,018 --> 00:02:27,981
They were clearly killed
to cover up what happened.

56
00:02:28,064 --> 00:02:31,609
Crime just keeps getting worse nowadays.

57
00:02:32,652 --> 00:02:34,237
Exactly.

58
00:02:34,320 --> 00:02:38,116
Even high-powered firearms are everywhere.

59
00:02:38,616 --> 00:02:41,286
What's happening in our country
is heartbreaking.

60
00:02:41,369 --> 00:02:44,455
And what's worse is, instead
of working together to find a solution,

61
00:02:45,039 --> 00:02:47,375
people are fighting.

62
00:02:48,501 --> 00:02:51,588
WERE THE 13 METAL LEADERS
DELIBERATELY KILLED?

63
00:03:02,515 --> 00:03:04,183
[sighs softly]

64
00:03:04,267 --> 00:03:08,396
[morose music playing]

65
00:03:17,655 --> 00:03:18,489
[Marcus] Ma.

66
00:03:19,574 --> 00:03:22,076
- Marcus.
- I'm sorry, Ma.

67
00:03:24,829 --> 00:03:28,917
Oh, sweetie, why are you apologizing?

68
00:03:31,127 --> 00:03:32,378
[exhales heavily]

69
00:03:33,838 --> 00:03:34,964
[sighs sharply]

70
00:03:36,341 --> 00:03:38,885
I wasn't able to stop them.

71
00:03:40,345 --> 00:03:43,139
[breathes heavily]

72
00:03:45,099 --> 00:03:49,312
Why can't I trace
and bring down that syndicate?

73
00:03:50,605 --> 00:03:53,191
How many more people have to die?

74
00:03:53,274 --> 00:03:55,443
How many more people
will fall victim to them?

75
00:03:56,110 --> 00:03:57,320
[Marcus exhales]

76
00:03:58,863 --> 00:04:00,240
You were one of them, Ma. [sighs]

77
00:04:00,323 --> 00:04:01,157
‪[Marcus sighs]

78
00:04:02,325 --> 00:04:04,535
- You got dragged into this too.
- [Teresa sighs]

79
00:04:05,119 --> 00:04:08,873
You're doing everything
you can to stop them, son.

80
00:04:10,375 --> 00:04:14,337
But you're up against powerful people.

81
00:04:14,420 --> 00:04:16,965
But you didn't give up, did you?

82
00:04:20,218 --> 00:04:24,847
[in English] There are just things
that are… beyond our control.

83
00:04:25,640 --> 00:04:27,976
Like what happened to me today,

84
00:04:28,059 --> 00:04:29,936
like what happened to your brother.

85
00:04:31,396 --> 00:04:32,230
‪[Teresa sighs]

86
00:04:33,231 --> 00:04:36,734
[in English] We can only do so much, son.

87
00:04:36,818 --> 00:04:43,241
At the end of the day,
what matters is you don't give up.

88
00:04:44,409 --> 00:04:47,745
You must never, never, never give up.

89
00:04:48,538 --> 00:04:49,956
I know that one day

90
00:04:50,039 --> 00:04:51,874
you will be able
to take that syndicate down,

91
00:04:51,958 --> 00:04:56,337
no matter how powerful they are.

92
00:04:57,338 --> 00:05:01,968
I know you won't stop until they're gone.

93
00:05:02,051 --> 00:05:05,847
- [pensive music playing]
- [Teresa inhales] Come.

94
00:05:14,188 --> 00:05:17,025
[stirring music playing]

95
00:05:24,657 --> 00:05:25,992
[Ahmad grunts]

96
00:05:29,871 --> 00:05:32,081
Sir, I don't think Reyes is involved.

97
00:05:32,165 --> 00:05:35,460
He's also trying to uncover
what really happened on the island.

98
00:05:36,294 --> 00:05:39,213
Maybe it's part of his cover.

99
00:05:40,423 --> 00:05:46,596
Or… maybe you've gone soft
because he saved your sister?

100
00:05:49,098 --> 00:05:51,976
I have a feeling they're
using him as the fall guy.

101
00:05:52,477 --> 00:05:54,020
He was suspended.

102
00:05:55,313 --> 00:05:57,398
He's also looking for Father.

103
00:05:58,107 --> 00:06:00,068
So I don't think he's in on this.

104
00:06:02,570 --> 00:06:04,113
What about his comrades?

105
00:06:05,323 --> 00:06:07,200
I'm still investigating them.

106
00:06:09,410 --> 00:06:10,411
[sighs] Alright.

107
00:06:13,372 --> 00:06:14,290
Sir.

108
00:06:16,959 --> 00:06:18,503
Why are you doing this?

109
00:06:20,755 --> 00:06:22,340
What do you mean?

110
00:06:22,423 --> 00:06:25,760
You're the President's Chief of Staff,

111
00:06:25,843 --> 00:06:28,304
yet you're investigating crime syndicates.

112
00:06:30,515 --> 00:06:31,432
Jalil,

113
00:06:32,183 --> 00:06:36,646
I want to know who’s
protecting these syndicates

114
00:06:36,729 --> 00:06:39,398
from within the SID and NLEA.

115
00:06:40,066 --> 00:06:44,779
The proliferation of weapons
has had a profound impact on our country.

116
00:06:44,862 --> 00:06:46,823
It is a national security threat,

117
00:06:46,906 --> 00:06:51,160
categorized as a clear and present danger.

118
00:06:51,744 --> 00:06:53,329
Is that really all, sir?

119
00:06:54,080 --> 00:06:56,624
Or maybe there's a deeper reason?

120
00:06:57,792 --> 00:07:01,504
I am not obligated
to tell you what I know.

121
00:07:02,296 --> 00:07:04,715
Obey my command.

122
00:07:04,799 --> 00:07:05,883
That's all.

123
00:07:05,967 --> 00:07:08,469
So I'm onto something, sir?

124
00:07:09,262 --> 00:07:16,102
Something bigger is happening
beyond selling weapons.

125
00:07:16,185 --> 00:07:22,483
Jalil, contact me
once you have something to report.

126
00:07:23,151 --> 00:07:24,902
[in Arabic] Peace be upon you.

127
00:07:28,698 --> 00:07:31,784
[tense music playing]

128
00:07:40,251 --> 00:07:44,130
DATU RAHMAN'S ARREST LED TO A MASSACRE!

129
00:07:44,213 --> 00:07:45,465
‪[intriguing music playing]

130
00:07:45,548 --> 00:07:48,426
[Marcus] <i>If I can't get answers from you,</i>

131
00:07:48,509 --> 00:07:50,887
<i>I'll uncover the truth some other way.</i>

132
00:08:19,123 --> 00:08:22,293
[morose music playing]

133
00:08:30,092 --> 00:08:33,387
Papa. It may be difficult,

134
00:08:34,722 --> 00:08:38,351
but I'm still pursuing our dream
of becoming a law enforcer.

135
00:08:39,185 --> 00:08:40,228
Sadly,

136
00:08:40,937 --> 00:08:44,732
even if you deserved it,
you didn't get the chance to fulfill it.

137
00:08:46,776 --> 00:08:48,152
Because just like me,

138
00:08:49,403 --> 00:08:50,738
you're a Muslim.

139
00:08:52,448 --> 00:08:55,368
Meanwhile, here I am.

140
00:08:56,619 --> 00:08:58,329
I've gotten into NLEA,

141
00:09:01,374 --> 00:09:04,168
but I seem so far away from promotions.

142
00:09:05,670 --> 00:09:07,922
But I won't give up hope.

143
00:09:08,881 --> 00:09:13,010
Because I know the time will come

144
00:09:14,554 --> 00:09:17,223
that they'll see our worth.

145
00:09:17,306 --> 00:09:18,933
That we have the ability to help,

146
00:09:19,016 --> 00:09:21,477
and that we're no different
from all of them.

147
00:09:22,186 --> 00:09:23,437
Especially now

148
00:09:24,939 --> 00:09:27,483
that I got included in Task Force Alpha,

149
00:09:28,776 --> 00:09:30,653
led by Marcus.

150
00:09:32,989 --> 00:09:34,824
I'm sure he's a fair leader.

151
00:09:36,075 --> 00:09:39,495
And Espina… He's the mysterious kind…

152
00:09:44,250 --> 00:09:45,751
but I know

153
00:09:47,795 --> 00:09:49,213
that he's a good person.

154
00:09:54,427 --> 00:09:57,346
Thank you so much for the guidance, Papa.

155
00:10:11,527 --> 00:10:14,155
[praying in Arabic] Oh, Allah.

156
00:10:14,238 --> 00:10:19,619
Forgive me and my parents
and have mercy upon them,

157
00:10:21,746 --> 00:10:26,709
just as they raised me when I was small.

158
00:10:35,509 --> 00:10:37,470
Sir. Out for lunch?

159
00:10:38,679 --> 00:10:40,973
Wow. This is my favorite spot.

160
00:10:41,557 --> 00:10:42,767
So, you love pork.

161
00:10:42,850 --> 00:10:45,686
They only serve pork here.

162
00:10:45,770 --> 00:10:47,730
What do you want, sir? It's my treat.

163
00:10:48,481 --> 00:10:50,232
One pork adobo, please.

164
00:10:50,316 --> 00:10:52,318
Suarez, I…

165
00:10:52,401 --> 00:10:54,111
I'd like to ask you something.

166
00:10:56,364 --> 00:10:57,823
[grim music plays]

167
00:10:57,907 --> 00:10:58,783
I knew it.

168
00:10:58,866 --> 00:11:01,535
What actually happened in Damai Island?

169
00:11:01,619 --> 00:11:03,287
Why did it fail?

170
00:11:08,709 --> 00:11:09,960
Suarez.

171
00:11:11,087 --> 00:11:12,463
All I remember, sir…

172
00:11:13,589 --> 00:11:15,674
is we were waiting to arrest Datu Rahman.

173
00:11:15,758 --> 00:11:17,385
Then, someone opened fire.

174
00:11:17,468 --> 00:11:19,929
- [tense music playing]
- [gunfire]

175
00:11:21,889 --> 00:11:23,849
Then, everyone else opened fire.

176
00:11:24,558 --> 00:11:26,060
Until it all fell apart.

177
00:11:27,436 --> 00:11:28,479
We got trapped.

178
00:11:31,190 --> 00:11:34,443
[gunfire]

179
00:11:34,527 --> 00:11:38,114
- [people screaming]
- [Jalil] Run!

180
00:11:38,948 --> 00:11:40,408
A lot of people died.

181
00:11:41,367 --> 00:11:42,952
Sir Marcus tried to control the situation,

182
00:11:43,035 --> 00:11:45,162
but the locals attacked us, too.

183
00:11:47,706 --> 00:11:48,958
[man screaming]

184
00:11:58,342 --> 00:12:00,094
But Sir Marcus told us something.

185
00:12:01,679 --> 00:12:02,847
Someone radioed in.

186
00:12:04,181 --> 00:12:08,185
And they said to neutralize the locals
because there are no civilians.

187
00:12:08,269 --> 00:12:09,687
[tense music playing]

188
00:12:11,689 --> 00:12:14,775
- [bullets whizzing]
- [morose music playing]

189
00:12:35,546 --> 00:12:37,548
And who said that?

190
00:12:37,631 --> 00:12:38,799
I don't know, sir.

191
00:12:38,883 --> 00:12:40,426
I didn't hear it, either.

192
00:12:43,471 --> 00:12:46,932
But Sir Marcus insists
that someone got into our comms…

193
00:12:48,559 --> 00:12:50,019
and sabotaged us.

194
00:12:50,102 --> 00:12:52,062
[tense music playing]

195
00:12:57,818 --> 00:12:59,653
And the radio…

196
00:13:01,322 --> 00:13:03,240
Who was supposed to hear that?

197
00:13:04,492 --> 00:13:06,410
Anyone near Sir Marcus.

198
00:13:08,370 --> 00:13:10,206
The ones who died.

199
00:13:13,250 --> 00:13:14,293
And the command center.

200
00:13:15,878 --> 00:13:17,004
Ma'am Lara.

201
00:13:17,963 --> 00:13:20,299
[music turns tense]

202
00:13:30,935 --> 00:13:33,145
Sir, don't get too sad now.

203
00:13:33,229 --> 00:13:34,813
I'm still alive.

204
00:13:34,897 --> 00:13:36,524
Oh. Jardin.

205
00:13:37,191 --> 00:13:38,526
Aren't you on leave?

206
00:13:39,443 --> 00:13:40,569
Why are you here?

207
00:13:40,653 --> 00:13:43,072
I'm fine, sir. It's nothing serious.

208
00:13:43,155 --> 00:13:45,324
You know how our job goes.

209
00:13:45,407 --> 00:13:48,661
Whatever happens,
we're still expected to be on-duty.

210
00:13:49,245 --> 00:13:51,455
- Right.
- You want some?

211
00:13:51,539 --> 00:13:53,374
[sentimental music playing]

212
00:13:53,958 --> 00:13:55,626
Oh, right. I forgot.

213
00:13:56,293 --> 00:13:57,586
I'll be in the office, sir.

214
00:13:57,670 --> 00:13:59,380
I still need to work on my reports.

215
00:13:59,463 --> 00:14:00,548
Okay.

216
00:14:06,428 --> 00:14:10,349
[Marcus] <i>And buddy,</i>
<i>while I'm on Damai Island,</i>

217
00:14:10,432 --> 00:14:14,144
<i>I'm going to turn off my cell phone,</i>
<i>so I don't get traced.</i>

218
00:14:14,228 --> 00:14:16,939
- <i>No one can know where I am.</i>
- [tense music playing]

219
00:14:17,022 --> 00:14:19,900
<i>I can't let anyone interfere</i>
<i>with my investigation.</i>

220
00:14:20,693 --> 00:14:22,528
[Usman] <i>I really hope so, buddy.</i>

221
00:14:22,611 --> 00:14:25,155
<i>I hope you can find the answers</i>
<i>you're looking for.</i>

222
00:14:25,865 --> 00:14:29,493
<i>So, we can finally bring justice</i>
<i>to our friends' deaths.</i>

223
00:14:30,160 --> 00:14:34,206
[tense music playing]

224
00:14:51,390 --> 00:14:52,766
[grim music playing]

225
00:14:52,850 --> 00:14:54,101
[indistinct chattering]

226
00:15:04,486 --> 00:15:05,487
[man] Just fine.

227
00:15:12,953 --> 00:15:15,539
[indistinct chattering]

228
00:15:19,710 --> 00:15:22,671
[Jalil] <i>Were you involved</i>
<i>in what happened to our island?</i>

229
00:15:23,464 --> 00:15:25,758
<i>I'll find out what you're hiding.</i>

230
00:15:54,286 --> 00:15:55,496
[ominous music playing]

231
00:16:06,340 --> 00:16:09,343
[tense music playing]

232
00:16:20,270 --> 00:16:24,483
<i>This specific gun was used</i>
<i>by a kidnap-for-ransom syndicate</i>

233
00:16:24,566 --> 00:16:28,445
<i>when they kidnapped a student last month.</i>

234
00:16:28,529 --> 00:16:31,365
<i>And this was used by a motorcycle rider</i>

235
00:16:31,448 --> 00:16:35,703
<i>when he killed another rider</i>
<i>whom he fought with last week.</i>

236
00:16:35,786 --> 00:16:37,663
<i>The other day,</i>

237
00:16:37,746 --> 00:16:41,917
<i>this is the gun that was being played with</i>
<i>by a seven-year-old child</i>

238
00:16:42,001 --> 00:16:46,630
<i>who accidentally shot</i>
<i>his three-year-old brother.</i>

239
00:16:46,714 --> 00:16:50,801
These are just a few among
the many illegal firearms

240
00:16:50,884 --> 00:16:53,804
circulating recently
that are being used for crimes

241
00:16:53,887 --> 00:16:58,058
that often results in a bloody death.

242
00:16:58,642 --> 00:17:02,771
<i>The question is,</i>
<i>for a country such as the Philippines,</i>

243
00:17:02,855 --> 00:17:05,524
<i>where there is a strict law</i>

244
00:17:05,607 --> 00:17:07,651
<i>regarding gun ownership,</i>

245
00:17:07,735 --> 00:17:10,821
<i>why is there a number of illegal sellers</i>
<i>on the black market?</i>

246
00:17:10,904 --> 00:17:14,825
<i>Who is the mastermind</i>
<i>of illegally distributing these firearms,</i>

247
00:17:14,908 --> 00:17:18,245
<i>and what is their motive in doing so?</i>

248
00:17:18,996 --> 00:17:23,292
Criminals nowadays have no fear.

249
00:17:23,375 --> 00:17:26,795
Their firepower is already up to par

250
00:17:26,879 --> 00:17:32,551
with the standards of our police
and our military.

251
00:17:33,260 --> 00:17:34,428
<i>Theirs might even be stronger.</i>

252
00:17:34,511 --> 00:17:38,307
General, what are the implications of this
on the confirmed Japanese Investment Deal?

253
00:17:38,390 --> 00:17:41,894
[in English] All we can do
is hope for the best. [laughs]

254
00:17:41,977 --> 00:17:48,150
If even the simplest of robbers
possess an RPG,

255
00:17:48,233 --> 00:17:51,653
<i>then what else could stop these syndicates</i>

256
00:17:51,737 --> 00:17:54,281
<i>from doing even more extreme crimes?</i>

257
00:17:54,364 --> 00:17:57,493
[reporter] <i>Shouldn't the NLEA</i>
<i>and SID do something about this?</i>

258
00:17:57,576 --> 00:18:00,287
[Manuel] <i>Of course they should!</i>

259
00:18:00,370 --> 00:18:03,624
[in English] <i>This is a matter</i>
<i>of national security.</i>

260
00:18:03,707 --> 00:18:07,127
They play a big role in this issue.

261
00:18:07,211 --> 00:18:09,546
[Manuel, in English]
<i>They have to take action!</i>

262
00:18:09,630 --> 00:18:12,341
[reporter] <i>As the former head of SID,</i>
<i>what can you say</i>

263
00:18:12,424 --> 00:18:14,426
<i>about the current head,</i>
<i>Director Azuelo's leadership?</i>

264
00:18:17,554 --> 00:18:21,642
[tense music playing]

265
00:18:25,229 --> 00:18:26,146
[knocking on door]

266
00:18:26,230 --> 00:18:27,898
[door clicks open]

267
00:18:27,981 --> 00:18:28,982
[in English] Sir.

268
00:18:30,442 --> 00:18:33,195
The markings and serial numbers
on the RPG have all faded.

269
00:18:33,278 --> 00:18:35,280
Even the bullets found
in the bodies of Axl

270
00:18:35,364 --> 00:18:38,283
and Jovi Rosales tested negative
on the ballistics.

271
00:18:38,367 --> 00:18:39,368
- [Lara sighs]
- [in English] Goddammit!

272
00:18:39,451 --> 00:18:42,454
They aren't part of the illegal shipment
that we're monitoring.

273
00:18:42,538 --> 00:18:44,081
[in English] I've been trying
to get in touch with Agent Reyes,

274
00:18:44,164 --> 00:18:45,457
but he's out of reach.

275
00:18:45,541 --> 00:18:47,835
Agent Reyes filed for an official leave!

276
00:18:47,918 --> 00:18:50,295
What? Marcus went on a leave?

277
00:18:50,379 --> 00:18:51,213
‪[Azuelo sighs]

278
00:18:52,089 --> 00:18:53,340
[in English] Sir.

279
00:18:54,049 --> 00:18:55,509
Yes? Do you need something?

280
00:18:55,592 --> 00:18:58,428
Looks like this is an important meeting,
so I wanted to join.

281
00:18:58,512 --> 00:19:00,305
- What's going on?
- [Azuelo, in English] Join in!

282
00:19:03,142 --> 00:19:04,601
Good thing you're here.

283
00:19:04,685 --> 00:19:06,645
Agent Reyes is on an official leave.

284
00:19:06,728 --> 00:19:10,607
In the meantime, I want
the two of you to team up.

285
00:19:10,691 --> 00:19:12,192
I want you to find out as soon as possible

286
00:19:12,276 --> 00:19:16,196
where the Rosales Brothers

287
00:19:16,280 --> 00:19:19,074
got their high-powered firearms.

288
00:19:19,158 --> 00:19:21,743
- [in English] Noted, sir.
- [in English] Yes, sir, copy on that.

289
00:19:25,789 --> 00:19:26,874
[Lara sighs]

290
00:19:32,004 --> 00:19:33,005
[in English] Sir.

291
00:19:33,088 --> 00:19:36,884
[grim music playing]

292
00:19:46,935 --> 00:19:50,731
[suspenseful music playing]

293
00:20:22,304 --> 00:20:23,347
[Felix grunts]

294
00:20:26,308 --> 00:20:27,351
[Felix sighs]

295
00:20:27,434 --> 00:20:28,352
Madam?

296
00:20:32,606 --> 00:20:33,607
Lara!

297
00:20:39,404 --> 00:20:41,907
[ominous music continues]

298
00:20:45,661 --> 00:20:47,120
- Agent Sam.
- [Sam] Hey.

299
00:20:47,663 --> 00:20:48,997
Where's Miss Lara?

300
00:20:49,081 --> 00:20:50,374
I haven't seen her around yet.

301
00:20:51,541 --> 00:20:52,584
Is that so?

302
00:20:53,126 --> 00:20:56,797
Agent Nica. Do you know
where Major Espina is?

303
00:20:57,589 --> 00:21:00,384
I haven't seen him around
the office today, sir.

304
00:21:02,010 --> 00:21:03,053
Is that so?

305
00:21:04,263 --> 00:21:05,222
Thanks.

306
00:21:11,687 --> 00:21:13,063
[indistinct]

307
00:21:14,439 --> 00:21:15,482
Where is everybody?

308
00:21:15,565 --> 00:21:16,608
Where is Sir Marcus?

309
00:21:16,692 --> 00:21:18,026
He's on official leave.

310
00:21:19,319 --> 00:21:20,946
Sir Marcus? On leave?

311
00:21:22,489 --> 00:21:24,741
Since when were leaves a thing for him?

312
00:21:24,825 --> 00:21:27,703
Wait a minute… Where is everybody?!

313
00:21:29,246 --> 00:21:31,748
[sarcastically] Well, isn't this great!

314
00:21:31,832 --> 00:21:33,417
Just where did those people run off to?

315
00:21:34,626 --> 00:21:38,171
- [tense music playing]
- [birds chirping]

316
00:21:57,816 --> 00:22:01,153
Gabriel! Don't let go! Hang on tight!

317
00:22:01,236 --> 00:22:02,237
Marcus!

318
00:22:02,321 --> 00:22:03,739
[young Marcus] Don't let go!

319
00:22:06,199 --> 00:22:09,328
[sinister music playing]

320
00:22:33,852 --> 00:22:36,396
[Marcus] <i>Everything started</i>
<i>on this island.</i>

321
00:22:37,522 --> 00:22:39,941
<i>That's why I know</i>
<i>I'll find the answer here.</i>

322
00:22:40,025 --> 00:22:42,736
[music intensifies]

323
00:22:59,002 --> 00:23:03,715
[Manuel] <i>We're about to move on</i>
<i>to the next stage of our plans, Lara.</i>

324
00:23:03,799 --> 00:23:07,302
[in English] I hope
you are in the right state of mind.

325
00:23:07,385 --> 00:23:08,970
[in English] Of course, Dad.

326
00:23:09,054 --> 00:23:10,889
[man] <i>Get inside. Now.</i>

327
00:23:12,724 --> 00:23:14,434
[Marcus] <i>We were set up</i>
<i>to ensure chaos on the night</i>

328
00:23:14,518 --> 00:23:15,977
<i>Datu Rahman was captured.</i>

329
00:23:16,061 --> 00:23:19,106
<i>And now, they're framing him</i>
<i>to be a criminal.</i>

330
00:23:19,189 --> 00:23:20,273
<i>But for what?</i>

331
00:23:20,357 --> 00:23:21,483
[suspenseful music playing]

332
00:23:21,566 --> 00:23:23,401
You are so careless!

333
00:23:23,485 --> 00:23:25,445
[Manuel] <i>That guy tailed you!</i>

334
00:23:25,529 --> 00:23:28,115
<i>And right towards here, in my very home!</i>

335
00:23:28,198 --> 00:23:30,700
Why did you have to fail now
of all times?!

336
00:23:32,494 --> 00:23:33,578
[Lara, in English] <i>How dare you!</i>

337
00:23:33,662 --> 00:23:35,580
<i>Why'd you follow me to my dad's home?</i>

338
00:23:35,664 --> 00:23:37,666
[in English] <i>Are you interrogating me?</i>

339
00:23:38,667 --> 00:23:41,044
[Marcus] <i>What's their true intentions</i>
<i>in all this?</i>

340
00:23:42,337 --> 00:23:44,798
[suspenseful music playing]

341
00:23:50,971 --> 00:23:52,848
[mysterious theme music playing]
